vgkkonda wrote:

&gt; In a class I have  5 testcases now i dont want to run all 5 test
&gt; cases. I want to run only 3 test cases say test1 test3 test5 cases
&gt; how this can be done.

1. Create a new class.
2. Add a &quot;custom suite() method.&quot;

public class JustThreeTests {
     public static Test suite() {
         //...
     }
}

3. Create a suite with just those three tests.

public class JustThreeTests {
     public static Test suite() {
         TestSuite suite = new TestSuite(&quot;Your descriptive name here&quot;);

         suite.addTest(new MyTestCase(&quot;test1&quot;));
         suite.addTest(new MyTestCase(&quot;test3&quot;));
         suite.addTest(new MyTestCase(&quot;test5&quot;));

         return suite;
     }
}

Now run the test runner on JustThreeTests. Done.
